<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in a few well-chosen words • in a few words</xh5><p> <i>in a few well-chosen words—</i>said of a short and effective utterance: He managed to say <u>in a few well-chosen words</u> what others might not convey in a half-hour speech.</p><p> <i>in a few words—</i>1. said of smth. stated very briefly: <u>In a few words</u> Captain Schley gave me an inkling of his plans. 2. in short; by way of summary: <u>In a few words</u>, they believe that individual freedom is the fundamental value that must underlie all social relations.</p><p> <i>See also: not in so many words / without many words.</i></p> </entry>
